title: $A lower as September US rate rise looms
text:
Wed, Aug 5, 2015, 12:43 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 3 hrs 17 mins $A lower as September US rate rise looms AAP â€“ 30 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar is lower after comments from US central bank official lifted expectations of a rate hike in September. 
At 1200 AEST on Wednesday, the currency was trading at 73.62 US cents, down from 73.77 cents on Tuesday. 
Overnight, Atlanta Fed President Dennis Lockhart said it would take a significant deterioration in the economic picture for him to not move ahead with a rate rise, sending the greenback higher. 
KEY MOVEMENTS: 
* 73.62 US cents, from 73.77 cents on Tuesday 
* 91.59 Japanese yen, from 91.46 yen 
* 67.78 euro cents, from 67.32 euro cents 
* 112.78 New Zealand cents, from 111.93 NZ cents 
* 47.38 British pence, from 47.28 pence 
Government bond yields: 
* CGS 5.5pct Jan 2018, 1.943%, from 1.880% on Tuesday 
* CGS 4.25pct April 2026, 2.888%, from 2.816% 
* Sept 2015 10-year bond futures contract, at 97.150 (yield 2.850 pct), down from 97.230 (2.770 per cent). 
* Sept 2015 3-year bond futures contract, at 98.010 (1.990 pct), down from 98.080 (1.920 per cent) 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session, bond market closes taken at 1630 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS
